To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Please send us the police report and investigation material for the loss that occurred around 12440 South East 192 ST, Kent, WA, on 06/28/2024.
Kent PD officers responded to the accident scene- Report C24021825, Officer Tracy Dodd 206-423-3962.

My insured is ABF transport.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Steve with Custard Insurance Adjusters

title: University of Georgia Open Records Requests

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Georgia Open Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

1. Any and all Open Records requests submitted to the University of Georgia between April 1, 2024 and May 13, 2024, and the corresponding responses by the University of Georgia Open Records department (ugaopenrecordsrequest@uga.edu), Bob Taylor (btaylor@uga.edu), or any other employee acting on behalf of the UGA Open Records department.

Please also note that this request seeks public records wherever they may be found, including on devices or networks owned or operated by private parties. For example, if an employee uses a personal cell phone or social media account to conduct public business, records created, maintained, or held on the phone or account are public records subject to this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 3 business days, as the statute requires.
